45 // __cpp_exceptions is referred from
46 // https://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/libstdc++/manual/using_exceptions.html
47 // gcc < 5 does not define __cpp_exceptions but __EXCEPTIONS,
48 // Microsoft C++ Compiler does not provide an option to disable exceptions
49 #ifndef DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
50 #if __cpp_exceptions || __EXCEPTIONS \
51  || (defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__))
52 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 1
53 #else
54 #define DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS 0
55 #endif
56 #endif
57 
58 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
59 #define DNNL_TRAP() __builtin_trap()
60 #elif defined(__INTEL_COMPILER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
61 #define DNNL_TRAP() __debugbreak()
62 #else
63 #error "unknown compiler"
64 #endif
65 
66 #if DNNL_ENABLE_EXCEPTIONS
67 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) throw error(status, msg)
68 #else
69 #define DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, msg) \
70  do { \
71  fprintf(stderr, "%s", msg); \
72  DNNL_TRAP(); \
73  } while (0)
74 #endif

88 struct error : public std::exception {
89  dnnl_status_t status;
90  const char *message;
91 
96  error(dnnl_status_t astatus, const char *amessage)
97  : status(astatus), message(amessage) {}
98 
100  const char *what() const noexcept override { return message; }
101 
107  static void wrap_c_api(dnnl_status_t status, const char *message) {
108  if (status != dnnl_success) DNNL_THROW_ERROR(status, message);
109  }
110 };
111 
113 template <typename T>
114 class handle_traits {};
115 
129 template <typename T, typename traits = handle_traits<T>>
130 class handle {
131 private:
132  static dnnl_status_t dummy_destructor(T) { return dnnl_success; }
133 
134  std::shared_ptr<typename std::remove_pointer<T>::type> _data {0};
135 
136 protected:
137  bool operator==(const T other) const { return other == _data.get(); }
138  bool operator!=(const T other) const { return !(*this == other); }
139 
140 public:
150  handle() = default;
151  handle(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
152  handle(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
153  handle<T, traits> &operator=(handle<T, traits> &&) = default;
154  handle<T, traits> &operator=(const handle<T, traits> &) = default;
155 
159  explicit handle(T t, bool weak = false) { reset(t, weak); }
160 
164  void reset(T t, bool weak = false) {
165  _data.reset(t, weak ? &dummy_destructor : traits::destructor);
166  }
167 
169  T get(bool allow_emtpy = false) const {
170  T result = _data.get();
171 
172  if (allow_emtpy == false && result == nullptr)
173  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
174  "attempt to use uninitialized object");
175  return result;
176  }
177 
180  explicit operator T() const { return get(true); }
181 
183  explicit operator bool() const { return get(true) != nullptr; }
184 
187  bool operator==(const handle &other) const {
188  return other._data.get() == _data.get();
189  }
190 
194  bool operator!=(const handle &other) const { return !(*this == other); }
195 };

487 #define DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(enum_name) \
488  inline enum_name operator|(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
489  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
490  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
491  } \
492 \
493  inline enum_name operator&(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
494  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
495  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
496  } \
497 \
498  inline enum_name operator^(enum_name lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
499  return static_cast<enum_name>( \
500  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
501  } \
502 \
503  inline enum_name &operator|=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
504  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
505  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
506  return lhs; \
507  } \
508 \
509  inline enum_name &operator&=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
510  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
511  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
512  return lhs; \
513  } \
514 \
515  inline enum_name &operator^=(enum_name &lhs, enum_name rhs) { \
516  lhs = static_cast<enum_name>( \
517  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
518  return lhs; \
519  } \
520 \
521  inline enum_name operator~(enum_name rhs) { \
522  return static_cast<enum_name>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs)); \
523  }
524 
525 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(normalization_flags)
526 DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS(rnn_flags)
527 
528 #undef DNNL_DEFINE_BITMASK_OPS

667 struct post_ops : public handle<dnnl_post_ops_t> {
668  using handle<dnnl_post_ops_t>::handle;

671  post_ops() {

674  "could not create post operation sequence");

676  }
677 
679  int len() const { return dnnl_post_ops_len(get()); }

682  primitive::kind kind(int index) const {
683  error::wrap_c_api(index < len() ? dnnl_success : dnnl_invalid_arguments,
684  "post_ops index is out of range");

686  dnnl_post_ops_get_kind(get(), index));
687  }

791  void get_output_scales(int &mask, std::vector<float> &scales) const {
792  dnnl_dim_t count;
793  int c_mask;
794  const float *c_scales;
795  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_get_output_scales(
796  get(), &count, &c_mask, &c_scales),
797  "could not get int output scales");
798  scales.resize(count);
799 
800  mask = c_mask;
801  for (dnnl_dim_t c = 0; c < count; ++c)
802  scales[c] = c_scales[c];
803  }
804 
820  void set_output_scales(int mask, const std::vector<float> &scales) {
821  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_set_output_scales(get(),
822  (dnnl_dim_t)scales.size(), mask, &scales[0]),
823  "could not set int output scales");
824  }
825 
827  const post_ops get_post_ops() const {
828  post_ops result;
829  const_dnnl_post_ops_t c_result;
830  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_get_post_ops(get(), &c_result),
831  "could not get post operation sequence");
832  result.reset(const_cast<dnnl_post_ops_t>(c_result), true);
833  return result;
834  }
835 
837  void set_post_ops(post_ops ops) {
838  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_set_post_ops(get(), ops.get()),
839  "could not set post operation sequence");
840  }

984 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
985  cl_context get_ocl_context() const {
987  cl_context context = nullptr;
988  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_context(get(), &context),
989  "could not get a context handle");
990  return context;
991  }
992 
994  cl_device_id get_ocl_device() const {
995  cl_device_id device = nullptr;
996  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_engine_get_ocl_device(get(), &device),
997  "could not get a device handle");
998  return device;
999  }
1000 #endif
1001 
1002 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL
1003  cl::sycl::context DNNL_API get_sycl_context() const;
1005 
1007  cl::sycl::device DNNL_API get_sycl_device() const;
1008 #endif
1009 
1012  template <class primitive_desc>
1013  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd) {
1014  return query(pd, dnnl::query::engine);
1015  }
1016 
1017 private:
1019  static dnnl_engine_kind_t convert_to_c(kind akind) {
1020  return static_cast<dnnl_engine_kind_t>(akind);
1021  }
1022 
1023  template <class primitive_desc>
1024  static engine query(const primitive_desc &pd, dnnl::query what) {
1025  dnnl_engine_t engine_q;
1026  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd.get(),
1027  dnnl::convert_to_c(what), 0, &engine_q),
1028  "could not get engine from primitive_desc");
1029  return engine(engine_q);
1030  }
1031 };

1043 struct handle_traits<dnnl_stream_t> {
1044  static constexpr auto destructor = &dnnl_stream_destroy;
1045 };
1047 
1049 struct stream : public handle<dnnl_stream_t> {
1050  using handle::handle;
1051 
1053  enum class flags : unsigned {
1056  default_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1058  in_order = dnnl_stream_default_order,
1060  out_of_order = dnnl_stream_out_of_order,
1062  default_flags = dnnl_stream_default_flags,
1063  };
1064 
1065  stream() = default;
1066 
1069  stream(const engine &aengine, flags aflags = flags::default_flags) {
1070  dnnl_stream_t astream;
1071  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create(&astream, aengine.get(),
1072  static_cast<dnnl_stream_flags_t>(aflags)),
1073  "could not create a stream");
1074  reset(astream);
1075  }
1076 
1077 #if DNNL_GPU_RUNTIME == DNNL_RUNTIME_OCL
1078  stream(const engine &eng, cl_command_queue queue) {
1081  dnnl_stream_t astream;
1082  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_create_ocl(&astream, eng.get(), queue),
1083  "could not create a stream");
1084  reset(astream);
1085  }
1086 
1088  cl_command_queue get_ocl_command_queue() const {
1089  cl_command_queue queue = nullptr;
1090  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_get_ocl_command_queue(get(), &queue),
1091  "could not get OpenCL command queue");
1092  return queue;
1093  }
1094 #endif
1095 
1096 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL
1097  DNNL_API stream(const engine &eng, cl::sycl::queue &aqueue);
1102 
1104  cl::sycl::queue DNNL_API get_sycl_queue() const;
1105 #endif
1106 
1108  stream &wait() {
1109  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_stream_wait(get()), "could not wait a stream");
1110  return *this;
1111  }
1112 };
1113 
1114 inline stream::flags operator|(stream::flags lhs, stream::flags rhs) {
1115  return static_cast<stream::flags>(
1116  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) | static_cast<unsigned>(rhs));
1117 }
1118 
1119 inline stream::flags operator&(stream::flags lhs, stream::flags rhs) {
1120  return static_cast<stream::flags>(
1121  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) & static_cast<unsigned>(rhs));
1122 }
1123 
1124 inline stream::flags operator^(stream::flags lhs, stream::flags rhs) {
1125  return static_cast<stream::flags>(
1126  static_cast<unsigned>(lhs) ^ static_cast<unsigned>(rhs));
1127 }
1128 
1129 inline stream::flags operator~(stream::flags rhs) {
1130  return static_cast<stream::flags>(~static_cast<unsigned>(rhs));
1131 }

1504  desc() : data() {}
1505 
1511  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, format_tag aformat_tag) {
1512  validate_dims(adims);
1513  error::wrap_c_api(
1514  dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_tag(&data, (int)adims.size(),
1515  adims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &adims[0],
1516  convert_to_c(adata_type),
1517  convert_to_c(aformat_tag)),
1518  "could not initialize a memory descriptor by tag");
1519  }
1520 
1526  desc(const dims &adims, data_type adata_type, const dims &astrides) {
1527  validate_dims(adims);
1528  error::wrap_c_api(
1529  dnnl_memory_desc_init_by_strides(&data, (int)adims.size(),
1530  adims.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &adims[0],
1531  convert_to_c(adata_type),
1532  astrides.size() == 0 ? nullptr : &astrides[0]),
1533  "could not initialize a memory descriptor by strides");
1534  }
1535 
1539  desc(const dnnl_memory_desc_t &adata) : data(adata) {}
1540 
1542  //
1545  desc submemory_desc(const dims &adims, const dims &offsets) {
1546  dnnl_memory_desc_t sub_md;
1547  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_desc_init_submemory(
1548  &sub_md, &data, &adims[0], &offsets[0]),
1549  "could not initialize a sub-memory");
1550  return desc(sub_md);
1551  }
1552 
1554  desc reshape(const dims &adims) {
1555  dnnl_memory_desc_t out_md;
1556  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_desc_reshape(&out_md, &data,
1557  (int)adims.size(), &adims[0]),
1558  "could not reshape a memory descriptor");
1559  return desc(out_md);
1560  }
1561 
1564  size_t get_size() const { return dnnl_memory_desc_get_size(&data); }
1565 
1567  bool is_zero() const { return data.ndims == 0; }
1568 
1569  bool operator==(const desc &other) const {
1570  return dnnl_memory_desc_equal(&data, &other.data) != 0;
1571  }
1572 
1573  bool operator!=(const desc &other) const { return !operator==(other); }
1574  };

1711 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL && defined(DNNL_USE_SYCL_BUFFERS)
1712  template <typename T, int ndims = 1>
1717  cl::sycl::buffer<T, ndims> get_sycl_buffer(size_t *offset = nullptr) const {
1718  static_assert(ndims == 1, "only 1D buffers supported");
1719 
1720  void *handle_ptr;
1721  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_get_data_handle(get(), &handle_ptr),
1722  "could not get SYCL buffer object");
1723 
1724  // XXX: workaround for ComputeCpp
1725  // ComputeCpp fails to construct zero-range buffer
1726  if (!handle_ptr)
1727  return cl::sycl::buffer<T, ndims>(cl::sycl::range<1>(1));
1728 
1729  auto &buf_u8 = *static_cast<cl::sycl::buffer<uint8_t, 1> *>(handle_ptr);
1730  if (offset) *offset = 0;
1731  auto range = cl::sycl::range<1>(buf_u8.get_size() / sizeof(T));
1732  return buf_u8.reinterpret<T, 1>(range);
1733  }
1734 
1740  template <typename T, int ndims>
1741  void set_sycl_buffer(cl::sycl::buffer<T, ndims> &buf) {
1742  auto range = cl::sycl::range<1>(buf.get_size());
1743  auto buf_u8 = buf.template reinterpret<uint8_t, 1>(range);
1744  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_memory_set_data_handle(
1745  get(), static_cast<void *>(&buf_u8)),
1746  "could not set SYCL buffer object");
1747  }
1748 #endif
1749 
1750  // Must go away or be private:
1751  static dnnl_data_type_t convert_to_c(data_type adata_type) {
1752  return static_cast<dnnl_data_type_t>(adata_type);
1753  }
1754  static dnnl_format_tag_t convert_to_c(format_tag aformat) {
1755  return static_cast<dnnl_format_tag_t>(aformat);
1756  }
1757 
1758 private:
1759 #if DNNL_WITH_SYCL
1760  struct with_sycl_tag {};
1761 
1762  DNNL_API memory(with_sycl_tag, const desc &md, const engine &aengine,
1763  void *ahandle, bool is_usm);
1764 #endif
1765 };

1771  return !(a == b);
1772 }

1774  return b == a;
1775 }

1782 }

1784  return !(a == b);
1785 }

1802 struct primitive_desc_base : public handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t> {
1803  using handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_t>::handle;
1804 
1805  primitive_desc_base() = default;
1806 
1808  engine get_engine() const { return engine::query(*this); }
1809 
1811  const char *impl_info_str() const {
1812  const char *res;
1813  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
1814  get(), dnnl_query_impl_info_str, 0, &res),
1815  "could not query implementation info string");
1816  return res;
1817  }
1818 
1820  memory::dim query_s64(query q) const {
1821  memory::dim res;
1822  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
1823  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(q), 0, &res);
1824  return status == dnnl_success ? res : 0;
1825  }
1826 
1828  memory::desc query_md(query what, int idx = 0) const {
1829  std::vector<query> valid_q {query::src_md, query::diff_src_md,
1830  query::weights_md, query::diff_weights_md, query::dst_md,
1831  query::diff_dst_md, query::workspace_md, query::scratchpad_md,
1832  query::exec_arg_md};
1833  if (!std::any_of(valid_q.cbegin(), valid_q.cend(),
1834  [=](query q) { return what == q; }))
1835  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments, "invalid memory query");
1836 
1837  const dnnl_memory_desc_t *cdesc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query_md(
1838  get(), dnnl::convert_to_c(what), idx);
1839  return memory::desc(*cdesc);
1840  }
1841 
1844  memory::desc src_desc(int idx) const {
1845  return query_md(query::src_md, idx);
1846  }
1847 
1850  memory::desc dst_desc(int idx) const {
1851  return query_md(query::dst_md, idx);
1852  }
1853 
1856  memory::desc weights_desc(int idx) const {
1857  return query_md(query::weights_md, idx);
1858  }
1859 
1862  memory::desc diff_src_desc(int idx) const {
1863  return query_md(query::diff_src_md, idx);
1864  }
1865 
1868  memory::desc diff_dst_desc(int idx) const {
1869  return query_md(query::diff_dst_md, idx);
1870  }
1871 
1874  memory::desc diff_weights_desc(int idx) const {
1875  return query_md(query::diff_weights_md, idx);
1876  }
1877 
1878  // Separate versions without the index argument for documentation
1879  // purposes.
1880 
1882  memory::desc src_desc() const { return src_desc(0); }
1883 
1885  memory::desc dst_desc() const { return dst_desc(0); }
1886 
1888  memory::desc weights_desc() const { return weights_desc(0); }
1889 
1891  memory::desc diff_src_desc() const { return diff_src_desc(0); }
1892 
1894  memory::desc diff_dst_desc() const { return diff_dst_desc(0); }
1895 
1897  memory::desc diff_weights_desc() const { return diff_weights_desc(0); }
1898 
1901  memory::desc workspace_desc() const {
1902  return query_md(query::workspace_md, 0);
1903  }
1904 
1907  memory::desc scratchpad_desc() const {
1908  return query_md(query::scratchpad_md, 0);
1909  }
1910 
1912  engine scratchpad_engine() const {
1913  dnnl_engine_t engine_q;
1914  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_query(get(),
1915  dnnl::convert_to_c(query::scratchpad_engine),
1916  0, &engine_q),
1917  "could not get scratchpad engine from a primitive_desc");
1918 
1919  return engine(engine_q);
1920  }
1921 
1923  primitive_attr get_primitive_attr() const {
1924  const_dnnl_primitive_attr_t const_cattr;
1925  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_get_attr(get(), &const_cattr),
1926  "could not get attributes");
1927  dnnl_primitive_attr_t cattr;
1928  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_attr_clone(&cattr, const_cattr),
1929  "could not clone attributes");
1930 
1931  return primitive_attr(cattr);
1932  }
1933 
1934 protected:
1935  void reset_with_clone(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd) {
1936  dnnl_primitive_desc_t new_pd;
1937  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_desc_clone(&new_pd, pd),
1938  "could not clone primitive descriptor");
1939  reset(new_pd);
1940  }
1941 
1942  primitive_desc_base(
1943  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind)
1944  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind::undef) {}
1945 
1946  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
1947  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind)
1948  : primitive_desc_base(pd, prim_kind, prop_kind, prop_kind) {}
1949 
1956  primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
1957  dnnl::primitive::kind prim_kind, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1,
1958  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2) {
1959  // It is OK to pass an empty primitive descriptor
1960  if (pd == nullptr) return;
1961 
1962  dnnl_status_t rc;
1963 
1964  dnnl_primitive_kind_t c_prim_kind = convert_to_c(prim_kind);
1965  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
1966  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
1967 
1968  // Check that primitive kind matches
1969  dnnl_primitive_kind_t pd_kind;
1970  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
1971  pd, dnnl_query_primitive_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_kind);
1972  error::wrap_c_api(rc,
1973  "could not get primitive kind from the primitive descriptor");
1974  if (pd_kind != c_prim_kind)
1975  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
1976  "primitive descriptor operation kind mismatch");
1977 
1978  // Check that propagation kind matches
1979  dnnl_prop_kind_t pd_prop_kind;
1980  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(
1981  pd, dnnl_query_prop_kind, 0, (void *)&pd_prop_kind);
1982 
1983  // Something went wrong
1984  if (rc != dnnl_success && rc != dnnl_unimplemented)
1985  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
1986  "could not get propagation kind "
1987  "from the primitive descriptor");
1988 
1989  // Everything is fine
1990  if ((rc == dnnl_unimplemented && c_prop_kind1 == dnnl_prop_kind_undef)
1991  || (rc == dnnl_success
1992  && (pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
1993  || pd_prop_kind == c_prop_kind2))) {
1994  reset_with_clone(pd);
1995  return;
1996  }
1997 
1998  // We could get the propagation kind but there is a mismatch
1999  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments,
2000  "primitive descriptor propagation kind mismatch");
2001  }
2002 
2003 protected:
2004  using base = primitive_desc_base;
2005 };

2097  }

2123 inline std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> convert_to_c(
2124  const std::vector<memory::desc> &mems) {
2125  std::vector<dnnl_memory_desc_t> c_api_mems;
2126  c_api_mems.reserve(mems.size());
2127  for (const auto &s : mems)
2128  c_api_mems.push_back(s.data);
2129  return c_api_mems;
2130 }

2239  "could not create a sum primitive descriptor");

2272  memory::desc src_desc(int idx = 0) const { return base::src_desc(idx); }
2273 
2275  memory::desc dst_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(0); }
2276  };
2277 
2278  sum() = default;
2279 
2282  sum(const primitive_desc &pd) : primitive(pd.get()) {}
2283 };
2284 
2286 
2288 
2291 
2294 
2297 struct primitive_desc : public primitive_desc_base {
2298  using primitive_desc_base::primitive_desc_base;
2299 
2300  primitive_desc() = default;
2301 
2307  primitive_desc(const_dnnl_op_desc_t desc, const primitive_attr *attr,
2308  const engine &e, const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t hint_fwd_pd,
2309  bool allow_empty = false)
2310  : allow_empty(allow_empty) {
2311  dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t iterator = nullptr;
2312  dnnl_status_t status = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_create(&iterator,
2313  desc, attr ? attr->get() : nullptr, e.get(), hint_fwd_pd);
2314  if (!allow_empty)
2315  error::wrap_c_api(
2316  status, "could not create a primitive descriptor iterator");
2317  pd_iterator.reset(iterator);
2318  fetch_impl();
2319  }
2320 
2327  bool next_impl() {
2328  dnnl_status_t status
2329  = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_next(pd_iterator.get());
2330  if (status == dnnl_iterator_ends) return false;
2331  error::wrap_c_api(status, "primitive descriptor iterator next failed");
2332 
2333  fetch_impl();
2334  return true;
2335  }
2336 
2337 private:
2338  bool allow_empty = false;
2339  handle<dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_t> pd_iterator;
2340  void fetch_impl() {
2341  dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd = dnnl_primitive_desc_iterator_fetch(
2342  pd_iterator.get(allow_empty));
2343  error::wrap_c_api(pd != nullptr || allow_empty ? dnnl_success
2344  : dnnl_runtime_error,
2345  "could not fetch a primitive descriptor from the iterator");
2346  reset(pd);
2347  }
2348 };

3816 
3817  private:

3819  mean = 1,
3820  var = 2,

3822  memory::desc stat_desc(int kind) const {
3823  dnnl_batch_normalization_desc_t *p;
3824  error::wrap_c_api(
3825  dnnl_primitive_desc_query(get(),

4385 struct rnn_primitive_desc_base : public primitive_desc {
4386  using primitive_desc::primitive_desc;
4387 
4388  rnn_primitive_desc_base() = default;
4389 
4392  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind,
4393  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind)
4394  : rnn_primitive_desc_base(pd, prop_kind, prop_kind, cell_kind) {}
4395 
4397  memory::desc src_layer_desc() const { return base::src_desc(0); }
4398 
4401  memory::desc src_iter_desc() const { return base::src_desc(1); }
4402 
4404  memory::desc src_iter_c_desc() const { return base::src_desc(2); }
4405 
4407  memory::desc weights_layer_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(0); }
4408 
4410  memory::desc weights_iter_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(1); }
4411 
4414  memory::desc bias_desc() const { return base::weights_desc(2); }
4415 
4417  memory::desc dst_layer_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(0); }
4418 
4421  memory::desc dst_iter_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(1); }
4422 
4424  memory::desc dst_iter_c_desc() const { return base::dst_desc(2); }
4425 
4427  memory::desc diff_src_layer_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(0); }
4428 
4431  memory::desc diff_src_iter_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(1); }
4432 
4434  memory::desc diff_src_iter_c_desc() const { return base::diff_src_desc(2); }
4435 
4437  memory::desc diff_weights_layer_desc() const {
4438  return base::diff_weights_desc(0);
4439  }
4440 
4442  memory::desc diff_weights_iter_desc() const {
4443  return base::diff_weights_desc(1);
4444  }
4445 
4447  memory::desc diff_bias_desc() const { return base::diff_weights_desc(2); }
4448 
4450  memory::desc diff_dst_layer_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(0); }
4451 
4454  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(1); }
4455 
4457  memory::desc diff_dst_iter_c_desc() const { return base::diff_dst_desc(2); }
4458 
4459 protected:
4460  using rnn_base = rnn_primitive_desc_base;
4461 
4462  // Constructs an RNN primitive descriptor from a C counterpart while
4463  // checking that it actually describes the expected primitive.
4464  rnn_primitive_desc_base(dnnl_primitive_desc_t pd,
4465  dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind1, dnnl::prop_kind prop_kind2,
4466  dnnl::algorithm cell_kind) {
4467  dnnl_rnn_desc_t *rnn_d;
4468  dnnl_status_t rc;
4469  rc = dnnl_primitive_desc_query(pd, dnnl_query_rnn_d, 0, &rnn_d);
4470  error::wrap_c_api(
4471  rc, "could not retrieve rnn_desc from a primitive descriptor");
4472 
4473  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind1 = convert_to_c(prop_kind1);
4474  dnnl_prop_kind_t c_prop_kind2 = convert_to_c(prop_kind2);
4475  dnnl_alg_kind_t c_cell_kind = convert_to_c(cell_kind);
4476 
4477  bool ok = rnn_d->primitive_kind == dnnl_rnn
4478  && (rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind1
4479  || rnn_d->prop_kind == c_prop_kind2)
4480  && rnn_d->cell_kind == c_cell_kind;
4481 
4482  if (!ok)
4483  DNNL_THROW_ERROR(dnnl_invalid_arguments, "rnn descriptor mismatch");
4484 
4485  reset_with_clone(pd);
4486  }
4487 };

5768 inline primitive::primitive(const_dnnl_primitive_desc_t c_pd) {
5769  dnnl_primitive_t result;
5770  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_create(&result, c_pd),
5771  "could not create a primitive");
5772  reset(result);
5773 }
5774 
5775 inline primitive::primitive(const primitive_desc &pd) : primitive(pd.get()) {}
5776 
5777 inline void primitive::execute(
5778  stream &astream, const std::unordered_map<int, memory> &args) const {
5779  std::vector<dnnl_exec_arg_t> c_args;
5780  c_args.reserve(args.size());
5781  for (const auto &a : args)
5782  c_args.push_back({a.first, a.second.get()});
5783 
5784  error::wrap_c_api(dnnl_primitive_execute(get(), astream.get(),
5785  (int)c_args.size(), c_args.data()),
5786  "could not execute a primitive");
5787 }
